Type: Package
Package: bettr
Title: Calculate Shannon Entropy and Provide Optimisation Functions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Owen", "O'Connor", , "owen.oconnor.2024@mumail.ie", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Sorin", "Bivol", , "sorin.bivol.2023@mumail.ie", role = "aut"),
    person("Sean", "O'Leary", , "sean.oleary.2023@mumail.ie", role = "aut"),
    person("Ivan", "Cakic", , "ivan.cakic.2023@muail.ie", role = "aut")
  )
Description: This package will include 1 (or two) inbuilt dataset(s) on
    202* English Premier League Odds (and 202* Wimbledon odds).  These
    datasets will be "bettr" datasets.  This package will also contain a
    function to transform data frames into "bettr" datasets and a generic
    function to plot (and possibly predict()) "bettr" data.
